The PID controller successfully regulated motor response using real-time encoder feedback.

The system demonstrated:
- Stable PWM-based motor control
- Real-time encoder pulse tracking
- Improved response stability after PID tuning
- Reduced oscillations using derivative control
- Reliable feedback acquisition using interrupts

## Observations

- Encoder noise initially caused unstable readings.
- Pull-up resistors improved signal stability.
- Capacitor filtering reduced PWM noise interference.
- High proportional gain produced overshoot.
- Derivative tuning improved damping behavior.

## Current Limitations

- Single-direction motor control
- No graphical response plotting
- Manual PID tuning process

## Future Improvements

- Bidirectional motor control
- Anti-windup implementation
- Real-time RPM plotting
- GUI-based parameter tuning
- Wireless monitoring interface
